race.comment: Hard to go past ZAMBARDO (7) who keeps winning and looks set to measure up again. He's won his past three with the latest of them the best, scoring by 1.75 lengths as the $1.85 favourite at Sandown Hillside. Now drops 3.5kg off that and gets to 2000m which should only suit better. This is harder but it's certainly not littered with stars and he's the one going through the grades. MAKDANE (3) is racing in outstanding form and will take beating. Far too good here over 1800m two back, he stuck on gamely for a narrow defeat in this grade last time out, now getting to 2000m from the inside gate. PRINCE ERIC (5) has been okay in three runs back and should appreciate a more genuinely run race up in trip. Gets Shinn on and can improve. AUTUMN SLIDE (10) can mix his form but the win two back has him firmly in the mix.
